    // Option 1: Direct jump
    long long min_cost = abs(nums[L] - nums[R]);

    // Option 2: Path via closest moves to an intermediate node Y, then direct jump Y -> R.
    // Or path L -> Y (via closest moves) -> R (via closest moves).

    // We need the shortest path distance between L and R in the graph defined by:
    // Edges: i -> closest(i) with cost 1.
    // Additionally, we can jump from any reachable node X to R with cost abs(nums[X] - nums[R]).

